{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"AMALIA VITI"}},"about":{"html":"<p>I like to make things. I am fascinated with the way things work and have been a tinkerer for as long as I can remember. That cool place where technology, design, and creativity intersect is where I like to spend most of my time.</p>\n<p>I currently work as a <strong>software engineer</strong> at <strong><a href=\"https://www.lyft.com\">Lyft</a></strong>.</p>\n<p>If you'd like to get in touch, <a href=\"mailto:amalia.viti@gmail.com\" target=\"_blank\">email me</a>.</p>"},"projects":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"0549782c-0a1a-5316-a6fc-cc19b38c59b4","html":"<p>I created a smart mirror for my apartment. This display hangs in my apartment and displays information useful at a glance--current time and date, the day's weather forecast, personal calendar events, nearby subway times, Citibike dock availability, and daily scheduled reminders.</p>\n<h4>V1 (2016)</h4>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/8576a/mirror-v1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V1\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/893a4/mirror-v1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/bbf57/mirror-v1.jpg 200w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/260b8/mirror-v1.jpg 400w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/893a4/mirror-v1.jpg 800w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/25965/mirror-v1.jpg 1200w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/e54c8/mirror-v1.jpg 1600w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/7c0ed/mirror-v1.jpg 2400w,\n/static/a7284f89a91310f08b139a96f5ae28c1/8576a/mirror-v1.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>I created the first non-interactive prototype using an old Dell netbook, plastic two-way mirror, and a custom-made wooden frame.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/8576a/mirror-v1-inside.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V1 Inside\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/893a4/mirror-v1-inside.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/bbf57/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 200w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/260b8/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 400w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/893a4/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 800w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/25965/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 1200w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/e54c8/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 1600w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/7c0ed/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 2400w,\n/static/0eaa8cef006b753e1620c0bd72638f9c/8576a/mirror-v1-inside.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The software ran a Node.js server on the backend and a React.js front-end. Glancing at it while getting ready quickly became a part of my morning routine.</p>\n<h4>V2 (2018)</h4>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/8576a/mirror-v2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Mirror V2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/893a4/mirror-v2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/bbf57/mirror-v2.jpg 200w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/260b8/mirror-v2.jpg 400w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/893a4/mirror-v2.jpg 800w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/25965/mirror-v2.jpg 1200w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/e54c8/mirror-v2.jpg 1600w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/7c0ed/mirror-v2.jpg 2400w,\n/static/435b0261a3d3d90045f727b2253d5cb6/8576a/mirror-v2.jpg 3024w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<p>The newest version is interactive via voice recognition (albeit a very crude version of it, currently). It is an Electron app running on Raspberry Pi that also utilizes React.js for the UI and has a much larger 1080p display.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/projects/mirror/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Mirror","created":"2018","path":null,"description":"My mirror is smarter than yours.","featured":true}}},{"node":{"id":"6b8486ef-f672-5f27-8ed1-42023d4d2594","html":"<p>I led development of <a href=\"http://atlas.qz.com\">Atlas</a>, Quartz's <a href=\"http://qz.com/434425/atlas-the-new-home-for-charts-and-data/\">platform for discovering and sharing charts</a>.</p>\n<p>The site is built with React and Node.js and is <a href=\"http://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/04/21/react-to-the-future-with-isomorphic-apps\">isomorphic</a>. Quite the buzzword, but it means that the same React javascript components are rendered on the server-side as well as the client-side, which proved to be a huge convenience in terms of development. In the past, I've worked on projects that either forego server-side rendering of content completely (and rely solely on the API) and others that use two separate templates to render the same exact markup (PHP and underscore.js, for example). I introduced the team to Node.js and React + Flux while developing the site.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/projects/atlas/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Atlas","created":"2015","path":null,"description":"A platform for discovering and sharing charts.","featured":true}}},{"node":{"id":"a9f59248-fe9c-5c2a-8fcf-69327c88d559","html":"<p>I needed real-time subway data for a project I was working on so I created a Node.js library to access the real-time MTA subway train schedule API.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/mta-gtfs\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/npm/v/mta-gtfs.svg?style=flat-square\" alt=\"npm\"></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/mta-gtfs\"><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/npm/dt/mta-gtfs.svg?style=flat-square\" alt=\"npm\"></a></p>\n<p>It powers a subway widget in the current version of <a href=\"/projects/mirror\">Mirror</a> and has been downloaded ~2k times via npm.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/projects/mta-gtfs/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"MTA GTFS npm package","created":"2015","path":null,"description":"A Node.js NYC MTA API library.","featured":true}}},{"node":{"id":"c5cfc30d-110f-57c3-a130-9696acab0abc","html":"<p>WeatherCloud is an internet-powered hanging lamp that brings the weather inside your home. Inspired by an Etsy cloud lamp and the original prototype of <a href=\"http://www.richardclarkson.com/cloud/\">The Cloud</a> by Richard Clarkson (originally spied at SVA's Products of Design lab), I decided to design my own lamp that utilized live weather data to inform its owner of the current weather in their neighborhood. It currently lives happily in my apartment.</p>\n<p>Its electronic guts are comprised of a <a href=\"https://store.particle.io/?product=particle-photon\">Particle Photon</a> (like an Arduino) and a string of LEDs. It uses <a href=\"https://developer.forecast.io/\">Dark Sky Forecast API</a> for its live data.</p>\n<p>There are different light patterns to match each weather pattern. Here are a couple of examples:</p>\n<p>When it's a clear day, the cloud glows a warm red-orange...</p>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-version=\"4\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:8px;\"> <div style=\" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;\"> <div style=\" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;\"></div></div><p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\"><a href=\"https://instagram.com/p/t7pqqhM1aE/\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_top\">A video posted by aamaliaa (@aamaliaa)</a> on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2014-10-09T12:39:02+00:00\">Oct 9, 2014 at 5:39am PDT</time></p></div></blockquote>\n<p>and when it's raining, naturally, lightning flashes fill the cloud...</p>\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-version=\"4\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:8px;\"> <div style=\" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;\"> <div style=\" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;\"></div></div><p style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;\"><a href=\"https://instagram.com/p/3NOCSBM1T7/\" style=\" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;\" target=\"_top\">A video posted by aamaliaa (@aamaliaa)</a> on <time style=\" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;\" datetime=\"2015-05-28T01:06:28+00:00\">May 27, 2015 at 6:06pm PDT</time></p></div></blockquote>\n<script async defer src=\"//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js\"></script>","fields":{"slug":"/projects/weather-cloud/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"WeatherCloud","created":"2014","path":null,"description":"An internet-connected lamp that shows the weather.","featured":true}}}]}},"pageContext":{}}